## Investigation Steps

1. Identify the new process.
2. Review the parent process.
3. Check the command line.
4. Verify the executable path.
5. Look for suspicious child processes.
6. Determine whether the execution was expected.

---

## Conclusion

Process creation events provide visibility into program execution and help identify malware, scripts, and attacker tools.
